cking for this one. I got to go on my very first planes raid this weekend (tag along with GoL, they needed another melee class and I was still up) so I'm still a novice at this, but it seems like there's an awful lot of benifit that could come out of this.<br>
<br>
It would be nice to have a chance for some of PoJ's players to get some serious experience working in this type of environment. I can't vouch for the rest of you, but as a guild PoJ has almost no experience working outside of the basic play, since we've never before had the numbers or the resources to participate in large scale outtings before.<br>
<br>
Now, I watched first hand as one person's mistakes managed to kill off about half of the 30 people in Fear, and would really rather not have myself, nor any guildmates, be the ones who take that person's place. The more training that not only we, but all newer players who hit a level to participate in Naggy/Vox raids, the planes, etc. can get, the better. <br>
<br>
I think it would also be rather nice to have people trained up in leadership roles as often as possible. I know I really don't want to try taking 12+ people against someone like Sathir, or up to Hate, without a LOT more experience in leading a large group. And eventually, folks like Hareq will get sick and tired of having to be the ones coordinating all this. The more qualified people you have, the easier it will be to facilitate all the various needs we have.<br>
<br>
Just my 1.2cp worth<br>
